         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botan. Garden ¶ 23/5/62 ¶ Dear Mr Bentham. ¶  ¶ I hoped to have sent to you by this mail the remittance of £100 in aid of the work on Australian plants. But the Parliament has not yet passed...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.05.23</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 58.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black-edged; M's sister Bertha died on 7 September 1861.</p>
               </note>Melbourne botan. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">23/5/62</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mr Bentham.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hoped to have sent to you by this mail the remittance of £100 in aid of the work on Australian plants. But the Parliament has not yet passed the votes for my department nor indeed of most of the others; a new civil service bill affecting the estimates has however gone through the lower house &amp; thus it is likely, that the financial arrangements for the year will be completed in time for my transmitting the amount by next mail. In the 18. number (transmitted by this mail) of my Fragmenta you will see three new genera characterized, on which I would be glad to have your opinion.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">In B62.05.01 M erected <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Coatesia</seg> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">C. paniculata</seg>), p. 26; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Osbornia</seg> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">O. octodonta</seg>), p. 31 and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Streptothamnus">Streptothamnus</name>
                     </seg> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. moorei</seg>), p. 28.</p>
               </note> I altered the name of <name key="Leiosporum">Leiosporum</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Used as a deleted herbarium name, replaced by <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Lamprosporum</seg> on the sheet K 591210. M erected <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Streptothamnus">Streptothamnus</name>
                     </seg> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. moorei</seg>
                     <seg style="">)</seg> in B62.05.01, p. 28. See also M to G. Bentham, 26 August 1862, and notes thereto.</p>
               </note> given before to <name key="Streptothamnus">Streptothamnus</name>, after I have now received the flowers, which seem to point to <name key="Bixaceae">Bixaceae</name>, altho' the embryo is so small. Have you in your genera plantarum<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> considered my seemingly portulaceous genus <name key="Gunnia">Gunnia</name> with septical dehiscence? I described it in the report on Babbages plants.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B59.04.02, p. 9 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Gunnia">Gunnia</name> septifraga</seg>). See G. Bentham to M, 24 July 1862. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope to learn successively of the safe arrival of my normal plants. vize:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1 case pr Young Australia<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Young Australian.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> shipped 26 Dec. (bill of loading)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1 case pr Great Britain shipped 27 Jan (bill of loading)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1 case shipped pr Dover Castle 27 March care of Dr Thomson the surgeon of the ship (<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">no</hi>
               </seg> bill of loading)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1 case pr. Orwell, shipped 24 April (bill of loading)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall have an other case in readiness in a few days.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope you will carefully bear in mind my total adversity of seeing any herbarium Synonyms whatsoever published!<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Lucas (1995) for a discussion of M's concerns.</p>
               </note> Pray do not quote any of mine, even out of my catalogues, unless such are <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fully</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">established by Diagnosis. […]</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The manuscript ends at the bottom of a page without valediction.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Do you not think that I am fairly entitled to the priority of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Citrus Austra</hi>
               </seg>lasica, having independently described <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">it first</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">This sentence is written in the margin of the first page of the letter. M described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Citrus australasica</seg> in B58.06.01, p. 26. See Bentham (1863-78), vol. 1, p. 371.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
